						<div class="postbody">If they had a SA-1 style CPU in the original system, it would be capable to DMA the entire 16kB of sprites at once and still have a lot of time left over.  With the addition of 128kB of VRAM and an improved OAM, you can pretty much animate sprites any old way and not run into problems.</div>

